  <h2>Friends and family can help</h2>
  <p>Being diagnosed with diabetes can take time to adjust to and affect how you feel.</p>
  <p>Telling people you have diabetes can be difficult, but it will help them understand what you’re going through. Friends, family and colleagues can give you support and encouragement when you’ve just been diagnosed with diabetes or you’re struggling to manage it. </p>
  <h2>Speak to others with type 1 diabetes</h2>
  <p>There are many people with type 1 diabetes offering support and sharing their stories on forums, social media and in group meetings.
</p>
  <p>You don’t have to join in if you don’t want to, you can just see what people are saying.</p>
  <h3>Helpful social media channels and conversations</h3>
  <p>A good place to start is the groups run by diabetes charities. There's also the diabetes online community (#DOC). This is a group of people with diabetes and clinicians. You don’t have to sign up to see what people are saying.</p>
